    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>This plugin was originally written for a client, but may be useful for others. It simply creates a discrete banner when viewed on mobile. This banner can include a link, to a mailing list for example.<\/p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the plugin zip file using WordPress&#8217; plugin installer, or install the plugin through the WordPress plugins screen directly (search for &#8216;Mobile Banner Robin Phillips&#8217;)<\/li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; screen in WordPress<\/li>\n<li>Use the Settings-&gt;Mobile Banner screen to set the text and link URL<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>v1.6<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Security bug fix release. Fixes CSRF vulnerabilitiy which allowed attacker to trick admin user into changing settings.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>v1.5<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added &#8220;Open link in new tab&#8221; option<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.4<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added an optional close button<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h4>1.3<\/h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added option to set banner height<\/li>\n<li>i18n bug fixes<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n",
        "screenshots": "<ol><li><a href=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/mobile-banner\/assets\/screenshot-1.png?rev=2480299\"><img src=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/mobile-banner\/assets\/screenshot-1.png?rev=2480299\" alt=\"The settings page\"><\/a><p>The settings page<\/p><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/mobile-banner\/assets\/screenshot-2.png?rev=2480299\"><img src=\"https:\/\/ps.w.org\/mobile-banner\/assets\/screenshot-2.png?rev=2480299\" alt=\"The banner in use on a mobile phone\"><\/a><p>The banner in use on a mobile phone<\/p><\/li><\/ol>",
        "reviews": "<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">Responsive design ... and small screens, my solution. thx<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/ezuehlke\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/df91aa34c83393b9255a0989e9e4edd6?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/df91aa34c83393b9255a0989e9e4edd6?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/ezuehlke\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Erik Zuehlke <small>(ezuehlke)<\/small><\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">October 28, 2022<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">As nice as the responsive design is, but it sometimes really reaches its limits! \nThen \"get around\" that, a little bit, with this plugin!\n\nIn most responsive themes, a reduced header is displayed, then the current posts and then the side menu (used by me as an order structure). \n\nNow there is hint with the link to an info page! \nShort form: Please turn your phone ... or use the \"desktopview\" of your browser :) \n\nThanks for your PLUGIN!\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">Does Exactly What it Advertises<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/doublesama\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/c400519484d5eab907a27001c14b2f92?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/c400519484d5eab907a27001c14b2f92?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/doublesama\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">doublesama<\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">November 21, 2019<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">I honestly didn't think this plugin was going to be as good as it is. So many times plugins don't work as advertised, but this one is extremely simple and that's what makes it great.\n\nIf I could be so bold as to make a request for a future update: It would be nice to have the option to include an \"x\" button to the right side of the banner which would hide it. I'm using my banner for a call to action specifically targeted at mobile users, and I think it might be nice if they could close out of it if they aren't interested.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n\t<div class=\"review-head\">\n\t\t<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n\t\t\t\t<h4 class=\"review-title\">Super Awesome Banner<\/h4>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"star-rating\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 out of 5 stars\" data-title-template=\"%s out of 5 stars\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"><\/span><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<p class=\"reviewer\">\n\t\t\t\tBy <a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/pegasoftcorp\/\"><img alt='' src='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/8be26bb9fb3c7cb8606ec9302c1c8bf4?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g' srcset='https:\/\/secure.gravatar.com\/avatar\/8be26bb9fb3c7cb8606ec9302c1c8bf4?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-16 photo' height='16' width='16' loading='lazy' decoding='async'\/><\/a><a href=\"https:\/\/profiles.wordpress.org\/pegasoftcorp\/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">pegasoftcorp<\/a> on <span class=\"review-date\">August 30, 2019<\/span>\t\t\t<\/p>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t<\/div>\n\t<div class=\"review-body\">It's really simple and efficient. Loved it. Works perfectly for mobile screens.\nMy humble request to the developer to add an option to adjust the height of the banner in the next update.<\/div>\n<\/div>\n"
    },
